Russia Stocks Drop Most in Week as Oil Declines in New York

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-09-01T11:00:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/russia-stocks-drop-most-in-week-as-oil-declines-in-new-york.html
Russian stocks lost the most in
almost a week as oil, the country’s main export earner, dropped
in  New York .  The  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  declined 1 percent to 1,530.82 as of 2:32
p.m. in Moscow, the biggest intraday loss since Aug. 26. OAO
Lukoil, Russia’s second-largest oil producer, lost 0.9 percent.
The dollar-denominated RTS Index fell 1.2 percent to 1,681.27.  Oil fell in New York before reports that may show U.S.
manufacturing shrank in August for the first time in two years
while employment growth slowed, a sign demand for the commodity
may fall in the world’s largest economy. Crude for October
delivery lost 0.5 percent to $88.37 a barrel.  The Micex lost 9.3 percent in August, the worst of the
benchmark indexes in the so-called BRIC group of emerging-market
countries. Brazil’s Bovespa Index fell 4 percent,  India ’s Sensex
dropped 8.4 percent and the Shanghai Composite Index declined 5
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in Moscow at 
